This paper discusses energy-efficient scheduling of cloud application components, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of brownout, which is a technique used in software engineering (cs.SE) to temporarily degrade user experience to avoid overloads. The paper also mentions the use of Dynamic Voltage Frequency Scaling, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the deactivation of application optional components, which falls under the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper mentions the use of microservices, which falls under the category of Architecture (cs.AR).
